  "prompt": "Who are the Impractical Jokers?",
  "response": "The Impractical Jokers are a comedy group consisting of four friends from Staten Island, New York: James \"Murr\" Murray, Brian \"Q\" Quinn, Sal Vulcano, and Joe Gatto. They rose to fame with their hidden camera TV show on truTV, where they challenge each other to perform embarrassing and hilarious dares in public, with the person who refuses or performs the worst punishment facing consequences. They originally met as members of a comedy troupe called The Tenderloins in college and have been friends since high school. Their TV show premiered in 2011 and became very popular, leading to multiple seasons, live tours, and a feature film. Joe Gatto left the group in late 2021, and the remaining three continue to perform together.",
